# Milhouse Plugin - Environment Variables

# NOTE: No ANTHROPIC_API_KEY needed!
# Claude Code analyzes images using its built-in vision capabilities.

# Optional: Figma Access Token for automatic frame export
# Only needed if using /milhouse:export-figma command
FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN=figd_your-token-here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (optional, only if using Figma API)
# 2. Replace the placeholder value with your actual Figma token
# 3. Source it: source .env
# 4. Or add to your ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc for persistence
# 5. Alternatively, export Figma frames manually to .claude/figma-refs/
